# Use DSTopbar for Screen Top Bars

Always use the `DSTopbar` component from the design system instead of creating custom top bar implementations.

## Why

- Maintains consistency across all screens
- Reduces code duplication
- Ensures proper spacing, styling, and behavior
- Leverages tested and maintained design system component

## Implementation

**Import:**
```kotlin
import net.qualgo.kinshield.core.designsystem.component.topbar.DSTopbar
```

**Usage:**
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - Use DSTopbar
DSTopbar(
    showBack = true,
    onBack = { /* handle back */ },
    centerContent = {
        Text("Title", style = DSTypography.h4.medium)
    },
    trailingContent = {
        Icon(painter = painterResource(R.drawable.ic_close), ...)
    }
)

// ❌ BAD - Don't create custom top bars
Row(
    modifier = Modifier.fillMaxWidth().padding(...),
    horizontalArrangement = Arrangement.SpaceBetween
) {
    IconButton(onClick = onBack) { ... }
    Text("Title")
    IconButton(onClick = onAction) { ... }
}
```

## DSTopbar Parameters

- `showBack: Boolean` - Show/hide back button
- `onBack: () -> Unit` - Back button click handler
- `centerContent: @Composable () -> Unit` - Center slot for title/custom content
- `trailingContent: @Composable () -> Unit` - Right side slot for actions
- `onCenterClick: () -> Unit` - Optional center content click handler
- `onTrailingClick: () -> Unit` - Optional trailing content click handler

## Common Patterns

**Basic screen with title:**
```kotlin
DSTopbar(
    showBack = true,
    onBack = viewModel::onBackClick,
    centerContent = {
        Text("Settings", style = DSTypography.h4.medium)
    }
)
```

**With action button:**
```kotlin
DSTopbar(
    showBack = true,
    onBack = viewModel::onBackClick,
    trailingContent = {
        DSButton(text = "Save", onClick = viewModel::onSave)
    }
)
```

**Close button only:**
```kotlin
DSTopbar(
    showBack = false,
    trailingContent = {
        Box(
            modifier = Modifier
                .size(40.dp)
                .background(DSColors.surface1, CircleShape)
                .clickable(onClick = onClose),
            contentAlignment = Alignment.Center
        ) {
            Icon(
                painter = painterResource(R.drawable.ic_close),
                contentDescription = "Close",
                tint = DSColors.iconAction
            )
        }
    }
)
```
